      • busInterfaceName

        public static String busInterfaceName(ISSRExecutor ssrExecutor,
                                      String deviceName,
                                      int axisId)
        Retrieves the bus interface name.
        Parameters:
        ssrExecutor - The ssr execution interface of controller.
        deviceName - The name of the device.
        axisId - The zero-based axis number.
        Returns:
        The name of the bus interface, e.g. 'Thin4MAdapter'.
        This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

      • queryReferencingStateGmsSensors

        public static int queryReferencingStateGmsSensors(String deviceName,
                                                  ISSRExecutor requestService)
        Queries the referencing state of the GSM sensors for the given device by executing an GenericReadIO ssr.

        Note: The result of the underlying GenericReadIO ssr is a bit field where each bit represents the referencing status of one axis. The return value of this method is an integer representation of the bit field.

        Parameters:
        deviceName - name of device to query GMS referencing state for.
        requestService - request service to execute request on.
        Returns:
        the integer representation of the referencing state of all robot axes

      • queryReferencingStatePositionSensors

        public static int queryReferencingStatePositionSensors(String deviceName,
                                                       ISSRExecutor requestService)
        Queries the referencing state of the position sensors for the given device by executing an GenericReadIO ssr.

        Note: The result of the underlying GenericReadIO ssr is a bit field where each bit represents the referencing status of one axis. The return value of this method is an integer representation of the bit field.

        Parameters:
        deviceName - name of device to query position referencing state for.
        requestService - request service to execute request on.
        Returns:
        the integer representation of the referencing state of all robot axes

      • areAllAxesReferenced

        public static boolean areAllAxesReferenced(int bitField,
                                           int jointCount)
        Checks the referencing state of all robot axes.
        Parameters:
        bitField - the internal value of the sensors which contains the referencing state of all robot's axes
        jointCount - number of joints to check referencing state against
        Returns:
        true, if all robot axes are referenced
        false, otherwise

      • isAxisReferenced

        public static boolean isAxisReferenced(int bitField,
                                       int jointCount,
                                       com.kuka.device.common.JointEnum axis)
        Gets the referencing state for a single axis.
        Parameters:
        bitField - the internal value of sensors which represents the referencing state of a robot's axes
        jointCount - number of joints present at robot
        axis - the axis whose referencing state shall be queried
        Returns:
        true, if the axis is referenced
        false, otherwise
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if axis is null or axis is bigger than jointCount.

      • execSafetyCommandSSR

        public static void execSafetyCommandSSR(SSR ssr,
                                        ISSRExecutor ssrExecutor)
        Synchronously executes the given SSR on the given request service and evaluates the response. If the response does not equal SSR_SAFETY_COMMANDO_SUCCESSFUL, an exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        ssr - SSR to execute
        ssrExecutor - the request service to execute the SSR on
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the SSR response does not equal SSR_SAFETY_COMMANDO_SUCCESSFUL
